  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nAs #979 describes, users are having trouble verifying contract sources on Etherscan using the [hardhat-etherscan](https://hardhat.org/plugins/nomiclabs-hardhat-etherscan.html) plugin. This is because hardhat-etherscan [has not added our chain ID and API endpoints to their list of endpoints](https://github.com/nomiclabs/hardhat/blob/0625c12d7f2a75056218928f4f03411e50fad0ae/packages/hardhat-etherscan/src/network/prober.ts#L19-L33).\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\nIt would be great if someone could make a PR over on the [hardhat](https://github.com/nomiclabs/hardhat) repo adding our networks in the following locations:\r\n\r\nThe current list of supported chain IDs: https://github.com/nomiclabs/hardhat/blob/0625c12d7f2a75056218928f4f03411e50fad0ae/packages/hardhat-etherscan/src/network/prober.ts#L19-L33\r\n\r\nThe current list of API endpoints: https://github.com/nomiclabs/hardhat/blob/0625c12d7f2a75056218928f4f03411e50fad0ae/packages/hardhat-etherscan/src/network/prober.ts#L35-L76\r\n\r\nKovan info:\r\nChain ID: 69\r\nEtherscan API URL: https://api-kovan-optimistic.etherscan.io\r\n\r\nMainnet info:\r\nChain ID: 10\r\nEtherscan API URL: https://api-optimistic.etherscan.io\r\n",
